  "body": "Hello,\r\n\r\nI work for a company that broadcasts multiple eth transactions daily. We are currently looking to switch from GETH to Erigon.\r\n\r\nI had two questions around the txpool in Erigon and how it works. I saw it is not a fork of Geth\r\n\r\nIssue 1 Essentially:\r\n\r\n- We broadcast a transaction at times of gas spikes.\r\n- The ethereum execution layer lets us know the transaction failed to broadcast due to insufficient gas provided.\r\n- We keep increasing gas, but still not enough.\r\n- When gas spike comes down, we reduce our gas price, but the node remembers a previous transaction with a higher gas price is still in the tx pool, so it prevents it from being sent.\r\n\r\n\r\nMy question:\r\n- Does Erigon automatically re-broadcast transactions?\r\n- Does Erigon keep transactions in the tx pool if it was unable to be submitted?",
