    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "1. There is no such thing as “gas price” in txpool. Or you have N gas on-your-balance or not. “price of gas” is not involved and not tracked. \r\n2.  There is “base fee” in every new block header, this limit may work similar: increase/decrease may change which txs are ready for mining/rebroadcasting. So, txpool does re-calc things on every new block and rebroadcast what need. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTxpool rebroadcast all txs when they moving to “pending sun-pool”. See:  https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/wiki/Transaction-Pool-Design\r\n\r\n3. “ Does Erigon keep transactions in the tx pool if it was unable to be submitted?” if txn is valid, just not enough balance - it will be placed in some sub-pool (not pending) and will stay in txpool and re-calc related parameters until it get mined (found in new block). Each sub-pool has own configurable Limit. TxPool flush new txs to own db every 30sec. \r\n4. if tx is rejected (when trying to add) - it return reason and just rejected. ",
