    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "I see some flag `--txpool.pricelimit` it's mapped to `MinFeeCap` \r\nprobably you did mean this field, and txs also have `FeeCap` field.\r\n\r\nSo\r\n1. if sender balance doesn't pass this check - it's rejected: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon-lib/blob/main/txpool/pool.go#L773\r\n2. this field also taking into account when re-calculation of txn-related fields is happening inside txpool. For example - if new block changed sender's state: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon-lib/blob/main/txpool/pool.go#L1254 and https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon-lib/blob/main/txpool/pool.go#L1301\r\n3. Txs sorting (inside each sub-pool) taking in account MinFeeCap: https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon-lib/blob/main/txpool/pool.go#L2342",
